The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 08 March is 232,275 (26,771.1 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 03 March, there were 4,268 new confirmed cases (491.9 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 24 February, there were 4,364 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 2% (96 fewer cases).
